Alhaji Musa Umar, the kidnapped father-in-law to President Buhari’s ADC, has regained his freedom. A report on Tuesday morning by Channels Television quoted a security source within the Presidency who craved anonymity as disclosing that Umar was rescued in Kano. Umar, who is the Magajin Garin (Village Head) of President Muhamammadu Buhari’s hometown, Daura, was abducted at about 7pm on May 1, 2019 in his Daura residence, Katsina North, shortly after observing Maghrib prayer. (News Express)